TY  - JOUR
T1  - Competitive Advantage Through Artificial Intelligence: Toward a Theory of Situated AI
AU  - Kemp, Ayenda
Y1  - 2023/12/07
PY  - 2023
DA  - 2024/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2020.0205
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2020.0205
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 618
EP  - 635
VL  - 49
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - How can firms establish competitive advantages using artificial intelligence (AI)? Although AI is beginning to permeate business activities, our understanding of how AI can be used to create unique value is limited. To address this void, I introduce the concept of situated AI and illuminate its importance for establishing AI-driven competitive advantages. The paper highlights the organizational activities involved in situating AI?specifically, grounding, bounding, and recasting. It also explains the conditions in which these situating activities better enable firms to develop AI-driven capabilities that are firm-specific, cost-effective, and appropriate for opportunities in the strategic environment. Thus, this paper provides an integrative framework for connecting a firm?s AI pursuits to competitive advantage.
AB  - How can firms establish competitive advantages using artificial intelligence (AI)? Although AI is beginning to permeate business activities, our understanding of how AI can be used to create unique value is limited. To address this void, I introduce the concept of situated AI and illuminate its importance for establishing AI-driven competitive advantages. The paper highlights the organizational activities involved in situating AI?specifically, grounding, bounding, and recasting. It also explains the conditions in which these situating activities better enable firms to develop AI-driven capabilities that are firm-specific, cost-effective, and appropriate for opportunities in the strategic environment. Thus, this paper provides an integrative framework for connecting a firm?s AI pursuits to competitive advantage.
